annotationA: Adaptor protein complex 1, gamma subunit, isoform D; Protein transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: vesicle coating; cargo loading into clathrin-coated vesicle; synaptic vesicle coating; compound eye development; secretory granule organization; intracellular protein transport; neurotransmitter secretion
annotationB: Adaptor Protein complex 2, mu subunit is a component of the AP-2 adaptor complex, which recruits certain transmembrane proteins into clathrin-coated pits for endocytic internalization
